ai "string"
aj (ai)
ak "I believe programming should be more personal. Currently (2026), software tools are mostly developed by a few people in a central place and then used by many more people. However, you very rarely modify or customize your software tools. Even experienced programmers using open-source tools rarely look at the source code."
al (aj ak)
am (ah al)
an "enum"
ao "text"
ap (an ao)
aq "The current state is practical: It takes a lot of effort to build software, so naturally you need to bundle resources to create big projects. I like that this necessity to collaborate fosters social relationships and gets people to explore problem spaces together. However, there is also a place for more personal, customized, specialized, smaller software. This vision existed since the early days of computing: Alan Kay envisioned computers as \"personal dynamic media\", where every user feels comfortable to create, use, and customize tools. Orchard is my attempt at creating a personal computing medium."
